items.name: Bubble (Dandonfuga) | LoCon
items.description:
The OC Bubble from the artist Dandonfuga. Works best on 0.8-1.0. Training done on NAI.

This is a LoCon which can be placed in LoRA folder on Automatic1111 1.5+ so make sure to update otherwise place in Lycoris folder.

Trigger: "BubblesDandonfuga, hair buns, blue eyes" always needed, for accuracy add "toned, tan" or "toned, dark-skinned female" as tanned skin often doesn't work without helper tags.

Suggestions:

  • The hair color may fail sometimes since I tried to avoid baking in style, add "Pink hair" to fix.

  • Sometimes even with helper tags the tanned skin may not work and success varies between models.

    • I avoided overbaking the character as the style was already being absorbed due to limited variety in the data.

Cute hair buns and abs what more do we need in cute OCs, this was simpler character to get back into the rhythm before next bigger works. I hope you all enjoy.

Feedback and reviews are always appreciated.

items.description:
⚠️⚠️⚠️ PLEASE TRY BOTH VERSIONS AND TELL ME WHICH ONE YOU PREFER ⚠️⚠️⚠️

This will help me decide how I train the next version! Thanks!

Like what you see? Help me create more models by supporting my work. SDXL fine-tuning is expensive as fuck compared to SD1.5. 👌

❤️❤️ Support Here ❤️❤️

Want more details? Click on 'Show more,' and check out my images for prompt ideas!

Have fun with this model! 💦

Hi there!

Welcome to my alpha release of my general-purpose SDXL model.

It's very alpha, and it has many problems, like difficult prompting and a heavy bias towards particular faces and some almost readable watermarks. But for a first run, I think it's okay. It will get better at the next release, I promise! <3

I'm still in the experimental phase of figuring out the best hyperparameters for training, so there are two models. One is trained with a learning rate of 3e-6, and the other with 5e-6. I can't decide which one is better, so I've uploaded both. Please let me know which one you prefer!

The model works with Booru tags now, so keep that in mind when prompting. Now you can do stuff like "small breasts", "medium breasts", "large breasts" and so on. See my example pictures.

Look at this table to get a feeling for the tags the model is trained on, and feel free to experiment with them.

https://rentry.org/pyros-sdxl-tags

General prompting can be enhanced in the future, and it certainly will be. However, as shown by my example pictures, it can produce good results. I had to generate 70 pictures to get those 20 showcase pictures, so the rate of success is pretty decent, even if there's room for improvement.

Prefered resolution is 832x1216

What's next?

The next version will bump up the training dataset to 30,000 images and will be cleaned up, so there's no bias towards specific faces and stuff and will also understand what a titfuck is. It's probably ready in a month or so.

Some technical stuff:

Training framework: Kohya's on RunPod A100

Dataset: 20.000 images

Batch size: 4

Steps: 110.000 / 70.000

Learning Rate: 3e-6 / 5e-6

items.name: Assumi (World of Warcraft) NSFW
items.description:
Hello! Today we have second character from World of Warcraft - Human Warlock Assumi. It is original character of artist Shina but I suppose you know her from noname55 videos and Shina arts :3

NSFW Model

LoRA was trained on Animefull due to best compitability with all anime / 2.5D checkpoint models.

0.8 - 0.95 strength of Lora is the best radius. 

Clip skip 2.

Some necessary tokens for better experience:

Appearance:

Assumi, 1girl,

red hair, short hair, hair bun, lips, makeup, lipstick, yellow eyes, detailed face, jewelry, earrings,

optional (without outfit): choker

Sexy warlock outfit:
highleg leotard, shoulder armor, cleavage cutout, (fishnet gloves:1.1), fishnet thighhighs, high heels

optional: fishnet top

General advices for generating:

I recommend you next prompt order for NAI-based mixes (you can see it in my preview arts):

  1. (highres, high quality:1.2) ("masterpiece" and "8K" kill some concepts. Be careful if you try some complex clothes or concepts.)

    Also put lighting / shadows, intricate details if you need some extra effects. Sometimes it doesn't work if style of anime or game was baked in LoRA or anime checkpoint mixes lost some concepts which exists in vanilla SD 1.5.

  2. Activation word (from lora civitai page, usually character name). Describe with danbooru tags character activity, expressions, camera position, background;

  3. Hair details, face details, jewelry, crowns, hats, etc.

  4. Clothes and shoes; Or nude.

  5. Body details (large breasts, cleavage). Genitals if you want to generate it.

Also LoRA trained with some NSFW poses. So you can try it with LoRAs or without it.

Advices for upscaling / fixing:

  • use highres.fix (If you are sure that your prompt is easy for SD); I prefer x4_Fatal_anime_500000_G, animesharp, foolhardy_remacri, siax with 1.5x - 2x upscale. 0.36 denoising and 15-18 Hires fix is enough.

  • Do not use "latent" upscaler because it works worse with denoisning < 0.5 but you don't want so high denoising stength because it changes your image instead of adding details.

  • use extention after detailer for better faces. It is better than inpaint.

  • use SD Upscale / Ultimate SD Upscale script in img2img after highres fix if you want 4K or more resolution with adding details (don't use Extras for it).

  • Use inpaint and sketch for other details;

  • Use Photoshop / Photopea extension for fixing hands, textures and other.

I will be glad to receive feedback from you and a demonstration of your art with my LoRA!

Other works.

  • Hires.fix: Latent (nearest-exact) Hires upscale: 1.5, Hires steps: 15, Denoising strength: 0.55

  • Clip Skip: 2.

  • Negatives: EasyNegative, (worst quality, low quality:1.4)

  • VAE: KlF8Anime2VAE_klF8Anime2VAE

Character Creation Example:

  1. Download LoRA.

  2. Prepare a character image and create a prompt using Tagger.

  3. Eliminate unnecessary prompts.

  4. Add prompts to achieve the desired composition.

  5. Adjust prompts while generating images, adding or removing as needed.


If you don't mind, I hope that those with different ideas can share their expertise.

Many thanks

items.name: Cordelia NotExist
items.description:
Who is she? The cool English Lit student? The beautiful PA? The political intern who's going all the way? She doesn't exist, except in this embedding.

I recommend you use ADetailer to show it at its best.

This uses the same method I describe here (i.e. take a face from stable diffusion and use it in FaceApp to map onto a dataset, and then use the data to train an embedding).

This one came from another character in my Big City Girls story on Deviant art (muscle growth, boob growth - though the embedding is her as a normal woman). Cordelia is one of the more beautiful characters in the story, so she's more glamourous than many of my previous emeddings, but she's still got a serious edge. She also wears glasses, which Faceapp only maps unreliably. I solved it by removing the glasses in faceapp to create the basic face, and then adding glasses in faceapp to some of the dataset, hoping the dataset will learn what glasses should look like on her face. It mostly seems to work, though that may be my imagination.
